  "prompt": "What causes night terrors?",
  "response": "Night terrors can be caused by several factors:\n\n1. Genetic predisposition\n- Family history of night terrors\n- Inherited sleep disorders\n\n2. Age\n- More common in children aged 3-12\n- Can occasionally occur in adults\n\n3. Sleep disruption\n- Irregular sleep schedules\n- Sleep deprivation\n- Stress\n- Fever\n- Fatigue\n\n4. Psychological factors\n- Anxiety\n- PTSD\n- High levels of emotional stress\n- Traumatic experiences\n\n5. Medical conditions\n- Sleep apnea\n- Restless leg syndrome\n- Certain medications\n- Neurological disorders\n\n6. Lifestyle factors\n- Alcohol consumption\n- Caffeine intake\n- Irregular sleep patterns\n- Excessive screen time before bed\n\n7. Brain chemistry\n- Imbalances in neurotransmitters\n- Disrupted sleep cycle regulation\n\n8. Environmental factors\n- Noisy sleeping environment\n- Uncomfortable sleeping conditions\n- Temperature extremes\n\nWhile the exact cause can vary, most night terrors are harmless and often resolve on their own, especially in children. Persistent or severe cases might require medical consultation.",
